Task 3: Number of Steps for Array Operations (6 pts)

Assume the array has 100 elements (N = 100).

Reading: 1 step (direct access using index)

Searching for a value not in the array: 100 steps (each element must be checked)

Insertion at the beginning: 100 steps (all elements must be shifted)

Insertion at the end: 1 step (insert directly)

Deletion at the beginning: 100 steps (all elements must be shifted)

Deletion at the end: 1 step (remove last element)


